HEADWORD: Winnebagoes
<hw>Win`ne*ba"goes</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <sing>sing.
<singw>Winnebago</singw> <pr>(<?/)</pr></sing>. <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld>
<def>A tribe of North American Indians who originally occupied the
region about Green Bay, Lake Michigan, but were driven back from the
lake and nearly exterminated in 1640 by the IIlinnois.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

